com.github.sviperll.adt4j

Annotation Type GeneratePredicate


  • @Retention(value=SOURCE)
 @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Documented
public @interface GeneratePredicate
    Generates predicate for specified case

    Predicate is used to test any ADT-value to find out if it represents some specific case.

    For example, isEmpty predicate can be used to test if given single-linked list is empty.

    Author:
    Victor Nazarov <asviraspossible@gmail.com>

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      MemberAccess access
      Java's access modifier for generated predicate.
      String name
      Name of generated predicate.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract String name
        Name of generated predicate.

        Name argument for GeneratePredicate annotation can be omitted. In such case visitor-interface method name with is prefix will be used. 

        
     interface ListVisitor<L, T, R> {

         @GeneratePredicate
         R empty();

         R prepend(T head, L tail);
     }

        isEmpty predicate will be generated in the example above.

        Returns:
        Name of generated predicate
        Default:
        ":auto"

        Java's access modifier for generated predicate.
        Returns:
        Java's access modifier for generated predicate.
        Default:
        com.github.sviperll.adt4j.MemberAccess.PUBLIC
